description:
The High Calling of Christians. Matthew 5:48 - &quot;be perfect&quot; etc. Jesus knew that no believer could attain perfection in this life (see 6:14,15). It is rather the measure and goal towards which we work, not to earn salvation - but instead to become fully mature in exercising those principles that Christ outlines in the preceding verses concerning love (Matthew 5:43-58).
